title: Creamy Garlic Chicken Pasta
instructions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and set aside.
Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken for 6-8 minutes per side until golden brown and cooked through. Remove and slice.
In the same pan, add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.
Pour in cream and bring to a gentle simmer. Cook for 2-3 minutes until slightly thickened.
Add cooked pasta and sliced chicken back to the pan. Toss to combine.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately while hot and creamy.

title: Mediterranean Quinoa Bowl
instructions: Rinse quinoa under cold water. Combine with 2 cups water in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes until water is absorbed.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork and let cool.
Meanwhile, dice cucumber and tomatoes. Thinly slice red onion.
Whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper for dressing.
Combine cooled quinoa with vegetables in a large bowl.
Add olives and crumbled feta cheese if using.
Drizzle with dressing and toss gently. Serve at room temperature.

title: Honey Glazed Salmon with Vegetables
instructions: Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
In a small bowl, whisk together honey, soy sauce, minced garlic, and ginger.
Place salmon fillets on prepared baking sheet. Brush with half the honey mixture.
Cut broccoli into florets and bell pepper into strips. Toss with olive oil.
Arrange vegetables around salmon on the baking sheet.
Bake for 12-15 minutes until salmon flakes easily and vegetables are tender.
Brush salmon with remaining honey glaze before serving.
Serve immediately with your favorite grain or rice.

title: Vegetarian Chickpea Curry
instructions: Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add diced onion and cook until softened.
Add minced garlic and ginger. Cook for another minute until fragrant.
Stir in curry powder and cumin. Cook for 30 seconds until aromatic.
Add crushed tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain and rinse chickpeas, then add to the pot along with coconut milk.
Bring to a simmer and cook for 15-20 minutes until sauce thickens.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Adjust spices as needed.
Serve over rice or with naan bread. Garnish with fresh cilantro.

title: Classic Beef Stir Fry
instructions: Slice beef into thin strips against the grain. Season with salt and pepper.
Cut bell peppers and onions into thin strips. Mince garlic and ginger.
Heat oil in a large wok or skillet over high heat until smoking.
Add beef and cook for 2-3 minutes until browned. Remove and set aside.
Add vegetables to the pan and stir-fry for 3-4 minutes until tender-crisp.
Add garlic and ginger, cooking for another 30 seconds until fragrant.
Return beef to the pan and add soy sauce. Toss everything together.
Cook for another minute until heated through. Garnish with green onions.

title: Lemon Herb Roasted Chicken
instructions: Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Pat chicken dry and season inside and out with salt and pepper.
Stuff cavity with lemon halves, garlic cloves, and herb sprigs.
Rub skin with olive oil and sprinkle with chopped herbs, salt, and pepper.
Cut potatoes and carrots into chunks. Toss with oil, salt, and pepper.
Place chicken in roasting pan surrounded by vegetables.
Roast for 50-60 minutes until internal temperature reaches 165°F (74°C).
Let chicken rest for 10 minutes before carving.
Serve with the roasted vegetables and pan juices.

title: Mushroom Risotto
instructions: Heat stock in a saucepan and keep warm over low heat.
Slice mushrooms and sauté in butter until golden. Set aside.
In the same pan, cook diced onion until translucent. Add garlic and cook 1 minute.
Add rice and stir to coat with oil. Cook for 2 minutes until edges are translucent.
Add wine and stir until absorbed. Begin adding warm stock one ladle at a time.
Stir constantly, adding more stock as each addition is absorbed (about 20-25 minutes).
Stir in cooked mushrooms and half the parmesan cheese.
Season with salt and pepper. Serve immediately with remaining cheese.

title: Thai Green Curry Vegetables
instructions: Heat 1/4 cup coconut cream in a large pan over medium heat.
Add green curry paste and cook for 2 minutes until fragrant.
Add remaining coconut milk and bring to a gentle simmer.
Add harder vegetables first (broccoli, bell peppers) and cook for 5 minutes.
Add softer vegetables (zucchini, mushrooms) and cook for another 5 minutes.
Stir in minced garlic and ginger. Cook for 1 minute more.
Season with salt and sugar to taste. Add lime juice if desired.
Serve over jasmine rice, garnished with fresh basil or cilantro.

title: Breakfast Egg Scramble
instructions: Beat eggs with milk, salt, and pepper in a bowl until well combined.
Heat butter in a non-stick pan over medium-low heat.
Add diced onions and bell peppers. Cook for 3-4 minutes until softened.
Add spinach and cook until wilted, about 1 minute.
Pour in beaten eggs and let them set for 30 seconds without stirring.
Using a spatula, gently push eggs from edges toward center, tilting pan.
Continue until eggs are almost set but still slightly runny on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and fold gently. Serve immediately while hot.

title: Sweet Potato and Black Bean Tacos
instructions: Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Peel and dice sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Toss sweet potatoes with olive oil, cumin, paprika, salt, and pepper.
Spread on a baking sheet and roast for 20-25 minutes until tender and lightly browned.
Meanwhile, drain and rinse black beans. Heat in a small pan until warmed through.
Warm tortillas in a dry pan or microwave until soft and pliable.
Mash avocado with lime juice, salt, and pepper to make guacamole.
Fill each tortilla with roasted sweet potatoes and black beans.
Top with guacamole, lime wedges, and any other desired toppings.
